<br>
'bloody exploding people and nudity'  <br>
<br>
    This concept is one of the features that make Anime and Manga so appealing.  Small film companies find it hard to get the special effects budget to do any justice to 'pulp' a person.  And large film companies are too concerned with audience size to attempt a quality blood bath.  Anime and Manga on the other hand can capture the essence of brutal slayings and there is a diversified enough audience to justify it.<br>
    Nudity and sex are a part of human nature, the Japanese are just more accepting of this notion.  *This is foreign media we're talking about, and a little understanding of their culture would go a long way in a better understanding of their media.    <br>
    Rumiko Takahashi, by no means, uses nudity gratuitously in the Mermaid series.  Yes, there is some violence, but this series is supposed to be a macabre.  The definition of macabre may shed light on this whole violence thing.<br>
    In fact, this entire discussion would be more reasonable if aimed at a movie like &quot;Kite&quot;.<br>
    As far as a review, the series is brilliantly written, and if you have any interest in horror manga, then I highly recommend it.  If you like this series, you will also enjoy &quot;Uzumaki: Spiral Into Horror&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uprismrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PrismRX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 6:48:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1883.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mermaid Flesh</span><hr size=1> What's 'Kite'? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uhcomiku.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HComiku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 8:02:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1883.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.h-comiku.com/hcban3.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mermaid Flesh</span><hr size=1> &quot;Kite&quot; is an anime about a vigilante organization that employs two teenage assasins to murder child molesters, using the latest in ballistic and explosive technology.  As you can guess by this brief description, it has very mature themes.  The English version is available, but it has been cut from 1 1/2 hours down to about 45 minutes, due to the graphic nature of the film. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=l